  "notes": "Intra Partum File 1, Group C (delivery outcome: Full Term / Pre-Term / Fetal Death / Abortion). Split config over the 'c' sheets (Q1c-Q4c). Province/HUC rollup (5 rows; region skipped). 3 meta cols; location NAME col 2. Bracket percentages divide by same-bracket Deliveries; totals by Deliveries Total. Abortion has NO percentage columns in the source (by design — abortion is treated as outside the delivery-outcome universe; the source's outcome=deliveries reconciliation deliberately excludes it). Deliveries columns (3-6) are cross-sheet refs to Group a, mapped to the shared INTRA_DELIVERIES_* codes (skip-unchanged dedups on commit). The full-term 10-14 percentage genuinely exceeds 100% in the NIR/Negros Occidental sample (a real source anomaly the DQC catches). Header letter duplication (Abortion reuses Fetal Death's n/o/p/q) is cosmetic. Annual sheet is a pure rollup, not ingested."
